
[1]transfusion

   TRANSFUSION, n. transfu'zhon. The act of pouring, as liquor, out of one
   vessel into another. In chimistry and pharmacy, transfusions of liquors
   are frequent.

   1. The act or operation of transferring the blood of one animal into
   the vascular system of another by means of a tube.
